SUBELEMENT T5 - ELECTRICAL PRINCIPLES
[4 Exam Questions - 4 Groups] 50 Questions

T5A Current and voltage: terminology and units, conductors and insulators, alternating and direct current
T5B Math for electronics: conversion of electrical units, decibels
T5C Capacitance and inductance terminology and units; Radio frequency definition and units; Impedance definition and units; Calculating power
T5D Ohm’s Law; Series and parallel circuits


Lab Equipment and parts
=============================================================================
multi-meter
breadboard with power board and hook-up wire
9v battery
resistor pack

=============================================================================

Demonstrate Ohm’s Law and Power Law
Formulas and images




Demonstrate the basic use of a multi-meter
Measure the voltage of the 9v battery (repeat with other batteries?)

Resistor color code.

Read (decode) the resistance of a resistor
Measure the resistance of the resistor and compare, checking tolerance (repeat)

Create a series circuit on the breadboard
Calculate the current of the circuit
Measure the current
Add another resistor in series
Calculate and then measure the total resistance and current
Calculate and then measure the voltage drop across each resistor.
Show that the current is the same through each resistor

Create a parallel circuit on the breadboard.
Read and Measure the resistors
Show that the voltage is the same across each resistor
Calculate and then measure the current through each resistor
